<FONT CLASS="ArticleHead"><BIG>Afternoon News Roundup</BIG></FONT>
<FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </FONT><FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthor">Csenicier</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=RIGHT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleTime>09/14/2001 03:46 PM CDT</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=LEFT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleText>
<B>Eight is enough?</B><p>Steve Burke, still firmly ensconced at Verant, <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000313.html">informs us</a> that we may have to wait awhile before embarking on our 8th Coldain Shawl quest.  The upcomming Shadows of Luclin expansion is, understandably, demanding his attention at the moment.<p><B>Those who fail to learn from history...</B><p>Mr. Burke also <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000314.html">comments</a> on reports that the war which spawns in the epic quest for the 10th Coldain ring begins an infinite loop.  Steve has yet to reproduce this effect.<p><B>For one brief shining moment...</B><p>Tann, our roving reporter extraordinaire, has informed us that EBWorld has changed the status of Dark Age of Camelot from coming soon to shipping on 10/9/01.<p><i>You can pre-order Dark Age of Camelot at <a href="http://www.ebgames.com/ebx/categories/products/product.asp?pf_id=209015">EBworld</a>.  It looks like a few of you may have noticed this already, since DAoC has already been awarded BEST SELLER bragging rights...</i><p><b>Legends never die</b><p>FoH and Furor <a href="http://www.noows.com/showthread.php?s=52b8694adbe354ac91dd383b2a7b5cae&amp;threadid=3414">move</a> to DaOC.  He also provides an unsolicited review.<p><B>Pets who look like their owners</B><p>The Iksars would <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000311.html">like to see</a> their pets be a bit more racially sympathetic.  Verant may need to go through a year or two of diversity training before they might oblige.<p>The Shaman epic is not working as intended and <a href = "http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000308.html">should be fixed</a> in the next patch.<p><B>Stealth uberfication</B><p>The Cloak of the Fire Storm <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=12156.topic">has received</a> a stealth haste boost in the last patch.<p><b>Haste quest in Stonebrunt</b><p><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/">Allakhazam's</a> lists a <a href="http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/quest.html?quest=1281">new quest</a> in the Stonebrunt Mountains that results in a <a href="http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/item.html?item=6610">haste sash</a>.  The Ranger's Glade has a <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/showthread.php?s=724a990b717b337a343faa9f0d11c751&amp;threadid=30235">discussion</a> about this as well.<p><b>Sleeping around</b><p>We <a href = "http://www.mobhunter.com/SiteChannelServlet.html?page=article&amp;articleid=562709230">recently reported</a> that Melalafen has appeared in the Western Wastes - a dragon apparently sympathetic to Kerafrym.  Blood of the Spider have solved a <a href="http://www.drow.org/news.shtml">quest</a> related to the dragon's appearance.  Details are sketchy but it appears that this quest is broken.  The Safehouse has an <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=8136.topic&amp;start=21&amp;stop=28">ongoing thread</a> on the subject.<p>Emil, a member of Blood of the Spider, had this to tell Mobhunter:<p><B>I am the first and only person to have completed the quest.<p>I did receive a reward.  It also is bugged.  I am in the midst of emails with dev /testing seeking some resolutions in the matters before we will consider going public with any information other to say that, Blood of the Spider did in fact, complete the Melalafen quest.<br></B><p>More as this develops.
</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
